Youths yesterday held peaceful demonstrations in Bungoma town to call for peaceful campaigns.The demonstrations came a day after Governor Kenneth Lusaka and his rival Wycliffe Wangamati were summoned by the IEBC over violence.The hundreds of youths were led by David Wekesa. They urged young people not to allow politicians to use them to cause violence. &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t be exploited, misused and dumped by the politicians. Remain peaceful and united as the country prepares for the August 8 General Election,&rdquo; Wekesa said. He said a woman was killed during a youth clash. Wekesa said the community regrets attempts by some politicians to take political power by force, resulting in loss of life and property.